The scattered particles were detected with
Si(Li) detectors, cooled to -25 degr., with
thicknesses ranging from 3 to 6 mm.
At low energies 1 mm thick surface-barrier
detectors were used.
The accuracy of the angle setting
The accuracy of the energy determination varied
between 200 keV at Ea = 40 MeV and 500 keV at
Ea = 100 MeV, at 120 MeV it was about 1 MeV.
Tbe energies of the incident beams were determined with
the conventional cross-over technique using 6LiF and
carbon targets.
The relative errors assigned to the cross
sections include the statistical error and the error
due to the uncertainty in the determination of the
scattering angle.  Absolute cross sections were
determined from the area of the elastic peak, target
thickness, solid angle, collected charge and the
correction for electronic dead time.
Whenever the statistical error was less than
5 % a value of 5 % was used in order to account for
uncertainties in the absolute normalization.

thicknesses amounted to 0.84, 2.47, and 4.94 mg/cm2.
